Origin

When The Spread had manifested on the surface of the Earth, Graham Sunderland volunteered for the U.S. Army to use his expertise on alternate mitochondrial energy systems on spread-infected humans. One day, he rescued a child, who later turned out to be immune for the infection by The Spread. Graham was opposed to experimenting on the child, but his collegues tranquilized him. Waking up, Graham was horrified to learn that his collegues had experimented on the child anyway. Taking matters into his own hands, Graham released The Spread from its containment cell and was himself infected by The Spread. But he turned out to be immune for it as well. Mentally broken, he became The Preacher.
name: The Preacher

deck: Orphaned at a young age, Garrett lived on the streets and had to steal to survive. This changed when he was spotted by a Keeper and trained in their ways. He then left their organisation and used their skills the become the world's greatest thief.
description:
Early life and training

"I was a kid. No parents, no home, running messages and picking pockets to keep my ribs from meeting my spine."

Living on the street with no parents and no home, Garrett had to deliver messages and pick pockets just to survive. This all changed when Garrett noticed a mysterious man walking by who nobody seemed to pay any attention to. Garrett figured the man must have had something valuable so he decided to sneak up on him and make a grab. He was caught in the act, however, and the man introducing himself as Artemis, a member of the ancient and secret Keeper order dedicating to observing the world and keeping the natural balance. He was impressed by Garrett's natural talent to be able to spot a Keeper and offered to take him in off of the street and train him in their ways. Until the age of twenty Garrett trained with the Keepers and was described as their "most promising acolyte", but left out of greed and used Keeper skills of stealth and evasion to benefit himself as the world's greatest Thief.
name: Garrett

deck: A mystic who toys with magic and was a love interest of Rory Regan
description:
Origins

Zipporah is a voodoo mystic, her name is the same as that of Moses' wife. She first meets Rory Regan in a bar, after he has moved to Louisina to avoid Gotham.

Creation

Zipporah first appears in Ragman: Cry of the Dead and was created by Elaine Lee and Gabriel Morrissette.

Major Story Arcs

Zipporah appears in the series Ragman Cry of the Dead and meets Rory Regan shortly after he has left Gotham to move to Louisiana, she is a young, beautiful and buxom woman who draws his attention easily. Through out much of the series she attempts to gain his love, even trying to cast a spell to have him think of her more (it is not specified if the spell ever works, it could be Rory's suit of souls protected him). The pair eventually fall in love. They share a bed and some romance but Zipporah deals in powerful magic with little concern for the consequences of her actions. Her charms, incantations and invocations draw the attention of the Loa Marinette and Marinette uses Zipporah's magic to first find bodies to possess. Later the goddess Marinette possesses Zipporah's form to use against Ragman as his suit and powers are the only thing standing between her and massacring much of Louisiana. Ragman, with the help of Legba and other voodoo mystics, is able to defeat Marinette and free Zipporah but all too late as the possession and exorcism weakened her body to the point of near death. On the brink of death, Zipporah asked Rory to absorb her soul into his suit so they could be together but he did not, so that her soul could be free. Zipporah was the third woman Rory Regan ever loved romantically (and according to him, the third he betrayed).

Powers & Abilities

Despite her carefree attitude towards magic, Zipporah shows some aptitude as she is able to create charms, has some powers of necromancy and can act as conduit for powerful magical beings. She is also good at simple trickery as she is able to use her beauty and amateur acting to trick some into paying for services regardless of any magic she intends to use or not.
name: Zipporah
